imate Anxiety and the Kid Question presents original research, drawing from in-depth interviews and national survey results that analyze the role of race in environmental emotions and the reproductive plans young people are making as a result. Sasser concludes that climate emotions and climate justice are inseparable, and that culturally appropriate mental and emotional health services are a necessary component to ensure climate justice for vulnerable communities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aClimatic changes. 0aHuman reproductionxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPopulationxEnvironmental aspects. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / Parenting / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520393844?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520393844423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520393844/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles